  "bib_entries": {
    "30485696": {
      "title": "Informed Prostate Cancer Risk-adjusted Testing -a New Paradigm",
      "abstract": "• Currently there is significant confusion and polarisation about prostate cancer screening for both patients and physicians alike. • We propose a risk-adjusted testing programme, which would lead to fewer patients who need to be tested and treated to save a life and also eliminate inappropriate prostate-specific antigen testing in the elderly and patients with severe co-morbidities where there is no clear benefit."
